Hillary Clinton fulfills right-wing nightmares by speaking directly to children at a June 15 event in Rochester, New Hampshire. Photo by Darren McCollester/Getty Images

This week, Hillary Clinton rolled out the first big policy proposal of her campaign: universal prekindergarten. Building on the Obama administration’s work on preschool for all children, Clinton endorsed programs to make affordable preschool available to low-income families and offer tax cuts to middle-class families with preschool children.
